!! The Genetic Paradox
What looks like ''altruism'' at the individual level (e.g., a mother risking her life for her child) is actually ''selfishness'' at the genetic level (the gene is protecting a copy of itself).

!! Types of Cooperation
* '''Kin Altruism:''' Helping those with shared genes.
* '''Reciprocal Altruism:''' Mutually beneficial cooperation between non-relatives ("Tit-for-Tat").
* '''ESS (Evolutionarily Stable Strategy):''' A strategy that, once adopted by a population, cannot be bettered by an alternative strategy (e.g., Doves vs. Hawks).